ing into the open again, marched up the slope. The boys saw that Jed was blindfolded, and that he carried an old-fashioned revolver in each hand.
\par "I hope one of those guns doesn't go off accidentally," murmured Chet, fearful that the weapons were loaded.
\par The initiate was led to a spot directly be\-neath the tree. Luke Jones stood in front of him.
\par "Now, Jed," he ordered, "you go ahead and do some exercises, holdin' dem two guns. Fust ob all, hold yo' hands up ovah yo' haid."
