\par "There they are! Grab 'em!"
\par The shot had been heard, and a crowd of farmers, attracted by the reports, had come to investigate. Immediately there was a rush toward the struggling figures in the road.
\par At the same time hoarse shouts summoned other members of the posse'. A roar of voices, a heavy tramping of feet, and the searchers swooped down. Chet was almost crushed un\-
derfoot, and found himself lost in the milling crowd. Ewald, Frank and Joe, on the other hand, were seized by rough hands and pulled to their feet.
\par Suddenly a woman rushed out of the Pennyweather house.
\par "Help!" she shrieked. "They've hurt Miss Pennyweather!"
